{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9a1d7581-a6e5-41e5-89b1-e7704582343d","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk **3.8**, the default test runner switched to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (the new `--` CLI runner). However, 3.x still shipped the VSTest adapter/bridge so `vstest.console` could still discover tests.\n\nIn **4.x**, the VSTest bridge is **no longer included by default**. That's why `vstest.console` finds zero tests.\n\n### You have two options:\n\n**Option 1 – Re-enable the VSTest bridge** (quick fix):\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Option 2 – Migrate your CI to the new runner** (recommended):\n\nReplace:\n```bash\nvstest.console MyTests.dll\n```\nwith:\n```bash\ndotnet test          # or\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --results-directory ./results\n```\n\nThe new platform supports `dotnet test` natively; no VSTest adapter needed.\n\nWould you like me to update your project file with either approach?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b68d5263-8618-4457-982b-c8862bad5e3a","outputTokens":341,"requestId":"A029:3A9E72:109582F:13AC2FE:69FEA568"},"id":"bc261477-199d-4b5c-833d-feb01c806172","timestamp":"2026-05-09T03:09:36.836Z","parentId":"a86fb143-7647-468b-86b8-0b3f8014e037"}
